	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 27th 12:43 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Barb Shammie here, currently Lvl 25- I've been 26 a few times but keep getting knocked back down. Why? The trip from Firiona Vie to Lake of Ill Omen, That's why. Is there another place for me to hunt and level quickly without having to deal with creatures like those darned Drachnids just to get to the hunting grounds. I don't get invis till lvl 29, and at this rate, that may never happen. L O I O is good for exp, but only if you don't lose it everytime you travel there. One major drawback is that I seem to experience a lot of lag in Firiona Vie. It's probably my antique computer that's slowing me down, so when I sight a Drachnid, even if a am running with Scale of Wolf, they catch me and Boom- I'm dead. I can't even cast gate cause they hit me so fast.<br>Any ideas?- Ohyeah, I'm working on my Totemic Armor quest right now, but I only have a few components so I'm open to suggestions. Thanks, Sabutant, Path of Valor, Cazic Thule Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
