<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=99101174940056></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99101174940056><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99101174940056>RE: Lvl 26, lvl 25, lvl 26, lvl 25</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=99101174940056#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 27th 9:02 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.12]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>LOIO is a very nice zone.&nbsp;&nbsp;If you are wanting to hunt here instead of trying somewhere else, here is what I would suggest.  Buy the Invisibility spell beforehand, stuff it in a backpack.  Stock up on food and water (fill a backpack or two), then make the trip to LOIO.  Bind at the FV zoneline, and stay until you hit 29.  If you find youself running out of food/water, just summon what you need.  I know it is tedious, but it will remove the need to travel back to FV.  Of course, this will require selective banking (aka avoiding heavy stuff).<br><br>You may also want to ask about a Camo/Invis from someone before you leave FV.  Most people are willing to do it if asked politely.  Taking the underground tunnel that surfaces near the Dreadlands tunnels is also a good idea, as it is closer to the Lazke zoneline.<br><br>One last general hint.  If you haven't already, turn down your clip plane.  This will help the preformence of older machines/video cards and can help avoid the lag/framerate choppiness.<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
