	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hi everyone,<br>A friend and myself are interested in pairing up from level 1... creation. I'm interested in making a Troll Shaman, and wondering what would the "best" (tongue firmly in cheek) partner for a Troll Shaman would be. <br><br>Here is a bit of background, sorry if it reads like a logic riddle-<br><br>I am partial to dark elves - especially shadow knights, though this might not be a big deal because I will probably be the one being the shaman. <br><br>If I am the shaman, I am certain my partner would prefer to be a melee class. <br><br>Should I be looking for 2 hybrids? Or should I be looking for 2 "straights"? Neither of us would want to be a Cleric, for instance. (again, since my partner wants to be a meleer). <br><br>Some of the combos I've been coming up with are:<br><br>Troll Shaman w/ DE Shadow Knight (shaman as range / healer / buffer) shad knight tanker w/both meleeing up front at first.<br><br>DE Necromancer w/ DE Shadow Knight (straight ahead rapage... bad thing would be the downtime & lack of healing between pulls, though the carnage time might make up for this?)<br><br>Trollie Shaman w/ ???????????<br><br>??????? Shaman w/ ???????????<br><br>Basically the whole gist of this is:<br>1. Not too much conflict with gear<br>2. Maximized killtime/downtime ratio<br>3. Longest amount of "fun" to be had before having to find a third.<br><br>Thanks in advance - <br><br>Frotteurist Bourreaux<br>DE Shadow Knight of the 24th<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
