	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would say that while in a perfect world this would be a cool idea to do, I don't think you would like it at all.&nbsp;&nbsp;The reasons are two:  If you get resisted on the first or second spell in the series, then it will mess you up.  Second, lets say you cast root, then a dot (and the dot helps break the root), then the mob will agro on you and interupt you while your macro is still trying to work.  It really is best to stick to a certain casting order and just cast each spell individually.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
