	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Fun with hotkeys!!<br><br>I am pretty sure you cannot make a hotkey to cast a series of spells, primarily because you have to recover from casting one before another can be cast.&nbsp;&nbsp;Even if it would work, you would still have to be standing for the duration of the casts.  But try it anyway.<br><br>Spell slots are numbered 1 thru 8 (going down).  Let's say your spells are memmed as such:<br><br>Root<br>Sicken<br>Tainted Breath<br>SoW<br>Healing<br>etc<br>etc<br>etc<br><br>Then you MIGHT load a hotkey with the following commands<br><br>line 1 -  /cast 1<br>line 2 -  /cast 2<br>line 3 -  /cast 3<br>line 4 -  /cast 4<br><br>But I'm positive it wouldn't work.  You will still be doomed to rooting, dot, med, dot, med, nuke, whatever.<br><br>Better use of hotkeys might be:<br><br>hotkey name - Root<br>line 1 -  /g ROOTING %t<br>line 2 -  /cast 1<br>_______________________<br><br>hotkey name - Dot-S<br>line 1 -  /g making %t so sick he's gonna puke.<br>line 2 -  /cast 2<br>_______________________<br><br>hotkey name - Dot-P<br>line 1 - /g poisoning %t boy is he screwed now.<br>line 2 - /cast 3<br>_______________________<br><br>hotkey name - HEAL<br>line 1 -  /g HEALING %t<br>line 2 -  /cast 5<br>_______________________<br><br>Making sense here?<br><br>Four different hotkeys, and your group knows what you're up to.  No one way you're going to have one button do it all (I DON'T THINK).<br><br>and my personal fave hotkey<br><br>hotkey name - HELP!<br>line 1 - /t   &gt;insert tank's name here&lt;  get this %t offa me or no more Badjur shammie buffs for jooo!!  <br>(heheh  leverage)<br><br>Have fun!<br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
