	   <tr><td colspan=2>look here, i don't know about all these people saying they 125 WIS and are not having any trouble, if that is true, then they are either :<br><br> A. level 12 or under.<br><br> B. not doing their job.<br><br> C. Die an awful, awful, lot.<br><br> Let me see if i can make this clear to starting shamen. WIS EQUALS MANA.<br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;       MANA = POWER<br><br> To the poster that said they are only ever at half mana so it doesn't matter, what a bunch of BALONEY. <br><br> Yes, it DOES matter, half of 100 for example is 50, with a low WIS index, half of 200 is 100,<br>with a HIGH WIS INDEX, even at half mana it is still DOUBLE the available mana of someone with a much lower WIS index!<br><br> Your goal, is to MAX your WIS at 200, then SLOWLY back off, to max your AC as much as possible, while retaining your WIS index of 200, or as close to it as humanly possible.<br><br> This requires a diligent and arduous search for the right pieces available in the game, but yes my friend, to a Shaman, WIS is king, and 200 is<br>your goal, after 40 if you dont have it, you are in for a world of hurt.<br><br> don't sacrifice a ton of AC for it, it can be done with a combination of the right pieces, but if you dont have at least 185 WIS or so by level 40, you are simply not going to be able to keep up, whether with canna , regen , and clarity or no, your TOTAL available mana pool will be so low at say 140 WIS that yoiur spell costs will be so high that to be effective your pull rate will have to be so slow before you go oom that no one will want you after you start slowing the groups pulls down , or even worse someone dies as a result of you going oom in a fight.<br><br> 200 WIS gives you your max mana pool at any given level, and it becomes increasingly important as you get higher, and anyone here or anywhere else who try's to tell you different is pulling your chain, clueless, or both.<br><br> Yes, in some situations you can get by with a lower WIS, but not below 185 or so past 40, and thats pushing it.<br><br> You are not a melee oriented player, you are caster oriented, and its kind of hard to cast with no mana, and low WIS equals low mana pool, is that clear?<br><br> Try this, take ALL you WIS gear off, and med to FULL. Then quickly put all your WIS boost gear back on, you should notice your mana bar drop WAAAAAY down, this represents mana gain, off your boost gear, which is your then, total available mana pool.<br><br> That means thats much more you can cast before going oom. When creating a shaman, you put EVERY POINT you can inti WIS it will let you, anything else, drop in stamina for HP.<br><br> Yes, if you didnt do this, you can maybe make it, but it ain't right, and it is not OPTIMAL.<br><br> Thats the way it is, and if anybody try's to tell you different, they are either just plain out wrong or trying to cover the fact that they created their character with crappy stats and are now trying to say it doesn't matter.<br><br> It does so matter, and the further along in game you go, the more obvious it will become if your total WIS index is way low.<br><br> Not trying to be a wise guy but thats the bare facts , go to any INT based caster board and try to sell them on the premise that 150 INT is as good as 200, and they will laugh you right off the Board, and just because Shaman have some limited tanking ability  and a  pet does not <br>change the fact that their / our primary role is a caster and to be the best you can at this requires you to have the largest mana pool you can get, and the way to do that is to obviously <br>have as high a WIS as you possibly can. <br><br> I hope all this is now clear to any people wanting to start a new shaman, and to the cluless wonder that downed iksar for a starting race because they were "weak" , you have got to be kidding me, high natural AC is a great asset, and high natural regen = constant mana  after 34 when you throw a regen on and the two effects "stack", then you use canna to convert regened HP to mana.<br><br> With the new Iksar armor drops in HATE , i'd be hard pressed to justify objectively anyone starting a shaman  that WASN'T iksar based solely on starting stats, not saying you CAN'T make another race work, but it wouldn't be OPTIMAL.<br><br> i love playing both my shaman and am trying to help, i cant believe some of the misguided info put up here, plse. people learn the FACTS about your Class and its attributes and abilities BEFORE creating one and if you didnt, well ,you <br>certainly are not the first one to have made that error,but please don't post here that "it don't matter", because yes, it DOES.<br><br> It is the difference between being good, and being the best. being most of what you can be, or being all of what you can be.<br><br>                Nebulonn  <br> <br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
