<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98989517495400></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98989517495400><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98989517495400>RE: Wisdom or strenght</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=98989517495400#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=492><span id=Sage>Gorthin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>149 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, May 14th 10:52 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.10]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Those starting points are not going to make or break your Shaman.&nbsp;&nbsp;What most people do not realize is that if you did not put &gt;any&lt; starting points into Wisdom, that means at ***level 50*** you will have 250 mana less.  That is one Superior Heal (which you get at 51) and it is not even a single Envenomed Bolt or Plague.<br><br>Having a high wisdom score is nice because it lets you have more maximum mana, and it helps reduce fizzles some.  But you are not doomed if you do not have a 200 wisdom by any stretch of the imagination.<br><br>If you look at Gorthin in my characters section, you will see I run at 184 wisdom with what I have.  That would be a 159 with no points into wisdom.  Lots of my decked out Shaman friends run with that wisdom or less, as they prefer ac/resists and they do not have mana problems.  All it does is allow a little more flexibility in equipment choices.<br><br>In reality you should/will never see FOM in a group at later levels.  I seldom see above 75m, unless I have a bard singing, Clarity II, and I am still cannabilizing for more mana.  As long as you can get a Slow off, and still have some mana for emergency heals, you are doing O.K. =)<br><br>Gorthin Spiritcaller<br>51 Shaman BB<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
