	   <tr><td colspan=2>No, Weissblau, this is not necessarily a huge mistake.&nbsp;&nbsp;Being a dumbass and not knowing what I was doing, I didn't put a single point into wis when I started my shaman (my first EQ char ever)...so my base wis is 80.  I was maybe level 25 by the time I truly had a good understanding of stats, by which time I felt it was too late to start another shaman, so I labored on.  Even if you don't put extra points into wis, it IS possible to get your wis up to an acceptable level.  Sure, some high end items are required, but it can be done.  With velium jewelry, gebs, imbued ivory earrings, reed belt, crystallised shadow tunic, Tserrina's Talisman, howling harpoon, spine chill spear, CGS, mammoth hide cloak, tot helm, lizzie mantle, and RMB's, I've managed to get my wis to 175.  It takes alot of work, patience and perserverance, but it can be done.  <br>&nbsp;<br>Badjur<br>54 Barbarian Shaman (Druzzil Ro)<br><br>Aepox Weeblatter<br>35 Dwarf Warrior</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
